com.rds_software.customers.menarini.projects.odp.backend.repos.csv

Class CsvOdpMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rds_software.customers.menarini.projects.odp.backend.repos.csv.CsvOdpMapper

  • public class CsvOdpMapper
extends Object
    Mapper class for converting between CSV records and ODP domain objects. Handles serialization and deserialization of Odp, OdpAuthorizationStep, and OdpCompany entities.
    Author:
    Claude Code

      • recordToOdp

        @Deprecated
public static Odp recordToOdp(org.apache.commons.csv.CSVRecord record)
        Deprecated. Use #recordToOdp(CSVRecord, java.util.Map, java.util.Map, java.util.Map, java.util.Map, java.util.Map, java.util.Map) instead
        Converts a CSVRecord to an Odp entity. Note: The model objects (OdpCurrency, OdpSupplier, etc.) are created as placeholders with only codes. Full descriptions should be loaded separately if needed.
        Parameters:
        record - the CSV record
        Returns:
        the Odp entity

      • recordToOdp

        public static Odp recordToOdp(org.apache.commons.csv.CSVRecord record,
                              Map<String,OdpCurrency> currencyMap,
                              Map<String,OdpSupplier> supplierMap,
                              Map<String,OdpCDC> cdcMap,
                              Map<String,OdpCompany> companyMap,
                              Map<String,OdpAccountVDS> accountVdsMap,
                              Map<String,OdpCDR> cdrMap,
                              Map<String,RoleType> userRoleMap)
        Converts a CSVRecord to an Odp entity with full reference data enrichment.

        This method creates an Odp entity from a CSV record and enriches reference data fields (currency, supplier, CDC, company, account/VDS, CDR) with their full descriptions by looking them up in the provided maps.

        Parameters:
        record - the CSV record containing ODP data
        currencyMap - map of currency code to OdpCurrency with descriptions
        supplierMap - map of supplier code to OdpSupplier with descriptions
        cdcMap - map of CDC code to OdpCDC with descriptions
        companyMap - map of company code to OdpCompany with descriptions
        accountVdsMap - map of account/VDS code to OdpAccountVDS with descriptions
        cdrMap - map of CDR code to OdpCDR with descriptions
        userRoleMap - map of userId to RoleType from user_roles.csv
        Returns:
        the Odp entity with enriched reference data

      • recordToAuthorizationStep

        public static OdpAuthorizationStep recordToAuthorizationStep(org.apache.commons.csv.CSVRecord record,
                                                             RoleType userRole)
        Converts a CSVRecord to an OdpAuthorizationStep entity. Note: This method creates an OdpUser with only the userId. The role must be populated separately by looking up user_roles.csv.
        Parameters:
        record - the CSV record
        userRole - the role for the user (looked up separately from user_roles.csv)
        Returns:
        the OdpAuthorizationStep entity

      • authorizationStepToValues

        public static List<String> authorizationStepToValues(String odpId,
                                                     int stepIndex,
                                                     OdpAuthorizationStep step)
        Converts an OdpAuthorizationStep to a list of CSV values. Note: userRole is not stored in authorization_flows.csv as it's a foreign key reference to user_roles.csv. Only userId is stored.
        Parameters:
        odpId - the ODP ID this step belongs to
        stepIndex - the index of this step in the authorization flow
        step - the authorization step
        Returns:
        list of string values for CSV writing
